Correction to Preregistration "Is there a sleep benefit in source memory? A model based analysis"


In the preregistration "Is there a sleep benefit in source memory? A model based analysis" by Sabrina Berres &amp; Edgar Erdfelder (2019, October 8, https://osf.io/2wsbj) three issues have been corrected:

1. Data collection procedure:
In the original preregistration, participants' compensation was described as follows: "For their participation, the participants will have the opportunity to take part in a raffle. Students from the University of Mannheim can receive course credits in addition." This description is ambiguous. Here a clear description: All participants have the opportunity to take part in a raffle. Students from the University of Mannheim can choose to receive course credits instead of the participation in the raffle.

2. Sample size:
In the original preregistration, a power (1-β) of .99 for all relevant parameters was reported. Following preregistration, an error in the model equations entered in multiTree for the post hoc power analysis was identified. Correcting this issue resulted in the following power:

D_large font (Probability of recognizing a target as old): .99;  
D_small font (Probability of recognizing a target as old): .99; 
R (Probability of judging the target as remembered): .99; 
d^R (Probability of retrieving the target's location and font size jointly for remember items): .57;
d^K (Probability of retrieving the target's location and font size jointly for know items): .33;
e^Dim1R (Probability of retrieving the target's location independent from the font size for remember items): .41;
e^Dim2R (Probability of retrieving the target's font size independent from the location for remember items): .35;
e^Dim1K (Probability of retrieving the target's location independent from the font size for know items): .24;
e^Dim2K (Probability of retrieving the target's font size independent from the location for know items): .23.

3. Data exclusion:
In the original preregistration, one exclusion criterion is missing: Participants in the sleep condition did not sleep between the learning and testing session. This has to be added to the list of exclusion criteria reported in the original preregistration.

